arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Major CE 363 earthquake leads to the collapse of the south gallery cryptoporticus of the Propylaeum West. The temple north colonnade falls from south to north across the Propylaeum, damage is incurred on the Propylaeum Retaining Wall and the entire area is overburdened with soil and debris.
3.75 m north south-by-1.20 m east west.
Soil fill between Locus 3 (later steps) and Locus 6 (earlier steps), and directly below Locus 4

Locus 5, Munsell No. 7.5YR5/6 (strong brown), consists of a coarse, loose, sandy soil with random inclusions of large, heavy stones (as well as pottery, bones, etc). This soil was most likely used as construction fill for the later steps.
Length of trench from Locus 1 to Wall K and entire width (east west) of trench.
Covering of the earlier steps with fill, sub-treads and later steps constructed.
